27/06/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) Interior Minister Darko Matijasevic said Sunday (26 June) that RS police are ready to arrest any war crimes indictee found on entity territory. Matijasevic added that his ministry is working to meet RS's obligations towards the UN tribunal and is collaborating with relevant authorities in Serbia-Montenegro and in the international community. The minister added that the RS government is also actively investigating alleged crimes committed against Serbs in the Sarajevo area during the war.
In other news, the BiH Association of Farmers organised weekend rallies in downtown Sarajevo and at the Raca border crossing, to protest the government's approach to problems in the agricultural sector. They also demanded urgent measures to protect domestic producers. (RTRS, Srna, Fena, NTV Hayat - 26/06/05; Nezavisne novine - 25/06/05)
